The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Thursday, May 19, 2005 

 Red tips balance in sport

 London, May 18 (Reuters): It triggers rage in bulls, denotes danger in traffic lights and is associated with losing control but in sports the colour red seems to gives male athletes the competitive edge.

 Weve shown, particularly in competitive and combat sports within the Olympic Games, that red appears to confer an advantage to the individuals wearing it, Russell Hill, of the University of Durham , said. Hill and his colleague Robert Barton found that if two athletes are closely matched in skill and ability, wearing red could tip the balance.




